Robert G. Isaman  Consultant, TechPrecision CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 8 different industries.See Board Relationships56--
Background

		Mr. Robert G. Isaman, also known as Bob, has been the Chief Executive Officer, Director, Chairman and President of Stanadyne Corporation since September 30, 2013. Mr. Isaman has been the President and Director of Stanadyne Holdings, Inc. since September 30, 2013. He has been an Operating Partner at Kohlberg & Company, L.L.C. since June 2012 and is responsible for investment thesis development, company diligence and portfolio management in the Industrial sector. Mr. Isaman ... has been a Consultant of Techprecision Corporation since March 31, 2017. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of Stolle Machinery Company, LLC from 2010 to 2012. He served as Chairman of Stolle Machinery Company. He served as the President of Terex Construction from 2007 to 2009 and served as President of Roadbuilding Divisions of Terex Corp. from January 2, 2007 to 2009 with responsibility with responsibility for divisions generating $2.7 billion in revenue that design, manufacture, distribute and provide aftermarket services for a wide variety of roadbuilding and construction vehicles and equipment. Prior to Terex, Mr. Isaman spent 21 years, from 1985 to 2006 at United Technologies Corporation and lastly served as its President of Fire Safety Americas, UTC Fire & Security in 2006. He was a member of United Technologies' Senior Executive Leadership team. He started in UTC's Otis Elevator Company in 1985 and advanced through the managerial ranks there. In 1993, he joined UTC International Operations as Deputy Program Manager of Russia and Commonwealth of Independent States. He returned to Otis Elevator Company in 1995 and served as its Vice President for Marketing and Field Operations - Asia Pacific Area since 2001. He served as the President at Otis Elevator (China) Investment Co. Ltd. from 2001 to 2002 as well as marketing and international operation positions in China, Asia Pacific and Russia with UTC. He served as a Green Beret in the U.S. Army. He is a Director and Chairman of Sabre Industries, Inc. He serves as on the Boards of Aurora Products Group, LLC. He also serves on the Advisory Board of Clearedge Power. He served as Executive Chairman of AGY Holding Corp. from February 01, 2013 to July 2013 and served as its Director from July 27, 2012 to July 2013. He served as an Independent Director at TechPrecision Corporation since November 20, 2012 until March 31, 2017. Mr. Isaman spent over 25 years in the manufacturing sector. He is a veteran of the U.S. Army Special Forces. Mr. Isaman holds an M.B.A. in International Business from George Washington University and a B.S. Degree in Marketing from the University of Maryland.Read Full Background




